1. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper deals with the problem of relay selection in wireless powered communication networks, which involves information transmission and processing. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper focuses on cooperative networks and relay selection, which are key topics in networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper proposes different relay selection schemes to minimize the outage probability, which involves system design and control. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper discusses the performance evaluation of the proposed schemes, which may involve multimedia applications such as video streaming. 
5. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The paper involves numerical simulations to quantify the performance of the proposed schemes, which may fall under the category of computational engineering.
